9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 529, L.D. 1299, “An Act to Prohibit the
10 Unsecured Storage of Handguns in Motor Vehicles”
11 Amend the bill in section 1 in §2017 in subsection 1 in paragraph C in the first line
12 (page 1, line 10 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "42" the following: ', except that
13 a motorcycle as defined in Title 29-A, section 101, subsection 38, a golf cart as defined in
14 Title 29-A, section 101, subsection 25-A and an all-terrain vehicle as defined in Title 12,
15 section 13001, subsection 3 are not considered motor vehicles for the purposes of this
16 section'
17 Amend the bill in section 1 in §2017 in subsection 4 in paragraph C in the last line
18 (page 1, line 28 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "and"
19 Amend the bill in section 1 in §2017 in subsection 4 in paragraph D in the last line
20 (page 1, line 30 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "duty." and inserting the following:
21 'duty; and'
22 Amend the bill in section 1 in §2017 in subsection 4 by inserting after paragraph D the
23 following:
24 'E. A person who is a federally licensed firearms dealer pursuant to 18 United States
25 Code, Section 923(a)(3) or a person shipping or delivering firearms to a federally
26 licensed firearms dealer.'
27 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
28 number to read consecutively.
29 SUMMARY
3300 This amendment adds exceptions to the prohibition against storing a handgun in an
3311 unoccupied motor vehicle, unless the handgun is stored out of plain view, for a federally
3322 licensed firearms dealer and a person shipping or delivering firearms to a federally licensed
